## HEARTH Funnel-facing reverse proxy (Track 2.0 minimal test case).
#
# HEARTH's gateway serves exactly one HTTP path (/mcp, streamable-http; see
# hearth/kernel/gateway.py's module docstring) and binds 127.0.0.1:8710 only.
# This proxy sits between Tailscale Funnel and the gateway so Funnel never
# exposes the bare gateway port directly to the internet: `tailscale funnel`
# targets THIS port, not 8710.
#
# KNOWN TRADEOFF (accepted 2026-07-21, trial-credit stakes): Google Agent
# Platform Studio's native "MCP Server" tool only offers Authentication: None
# today ("OAuth"/"API key" are both greyed out "Coming soon"), and sends no
# custom header at all. Since HEARTH requires X-Hearth-Key to identify ANY
# caller, this proxy stamps a FIXED key on every request that reaches THIS
# URL, so the secret HEARTH checks lives in a value only Studio's Endpoint URL
# field carries -- the Funnel URL itself is now the de facto shared secret,
# not a per-request header. Bounded by design: the caller this key resolves
# to (gcp-adk-test) is scoped to profile `research` (read-only) on
# `commandcenter` only -- worst case of the URL leaking is read access to
# public-ish docs/code, not a mutate path. Revisit once Studio ships API-key
# auth (then switch back to a real per-request header and drop this stamp).
#
# Also adds path narrowing (only /mcp is forwarded; everything else 404s) as
# defense in depth. No rate limiting yet (stock Caddy has none built in;
# deferred -- see the implementation plan's Track 2.0 §1 open decision).
#
# Run: caddy run --config hearth/etc/caddy/Caddyfile --adapter caddyfile

:8711 {
	handle /mcp* {
		reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:8710 {
			# HEARTH's gateway allowlists Host by value (loopback only,
			# ADR-0022's DNS-rebinding guard in gateway.py's
			# _transport_security) -- rewrite so the public Funnel hostname
			# the client actually sent doesn't get rejected as untrusted.
			header_up Host 127.0.0.1:8710
			# Stamped caller identity -- see KNOWN TRADEOFF above. Gitignored
			# snippet (same convention as start-hearth-gateway.cmd's
			# hearth/var/gateway.cmd): one `header_up X-Hearth-Key <value>`
			# line. This Caddyfile stays secret-free and tracked in git; only
			# the imported file under hearth/var/ carries the real key.
			# Rotate via `callerctl rotate` and update that file together.
			import ../../var/caddy-funnel-secret.caddy
		}
	}
	handle {
		respond 404
	}
}
